y=\"support-staff\"][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Team Members','','publish','closed','closed','','team-members','','','2017-07-11 15:46:33','2017-07-11 15:46:33','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?page_id=8689',0,'page','',0),(8691,1,'2017-04-06 11:14:26','2017-04-06 11:14:26','Nancy is the Communication Specialist at METS who has previously worked at Makerere University, Tetea Uganda and NSSF in various capacities in the communication field. She is the recipient of the Cranimer Mugerwa Best Photojournalist Award 2010, She is passionate about photography, writing, Public Relations and events management.\r\n\r\nShe holds a Bachelor?s Degree in Mass Communication and a Master?s Degree in International Relations and Diplomatic Studies from Makerere University. She has gained extensive experience in the Communication sector spanning over seven years. Her passion for detail and excellence topped with perseverance makes her well suited for a fast-paced events environment.','Nancy Karunganwa','','publish','closed','closed','','nancy-karunganwa','','','2017-04-10 12:29:33','2017-04-10 12:29:33','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=8691',2,'team-member','',0),(8692,1,'2017-04-06 11:24:42','2017-04-06 11:24:42','Edgar is the Project Coordinator for the HIV Case Based Surveillance (CBS) at the School of Public Health, Monitoring and Evaluation (METS) Program, Makerere University. He heads a project implemented in partnership with Ministry of Health (MOH). He is primarily responsible for setting strategic direction for the project in addition to serving as a bridge between METS management and CBS stakeholders. His over 10 years’ experience in HIV/AIDS programing and management has enabled a well-coordinated program. Edgar has vast knowledge of the National Health System management and has worked at Health Center IV, District hospital, District Health Officer and at the Ministry of Health.\r\n\r\nEdgar’s experience of working with USAID, CDC funded projects and the Government of Uganda (MoH) has equipped him with an excellent knowledge of both the PEPFAR and National reporting requirements. He has competences in data management, analysis and interpretation, reporting and presentation. Edgar holds a Master of Public Health Degree from the School of Public Health, Makerere University and a Bachelors of Medicine and Surgery from Mbarara University. Additionally, Edgar holds a Post Graduate Diploma in Monitoring and Evaluation (PGD M&amp;E) from Uganda Management Institute (UMI)','Dr. Edgar Kansiime','','publish','closed','closed','','dr-edgar-kansiime','','','2017-04-06 18:43:10','2017-04-06 18:43:10','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=8692',1,'team-member','',0),(8693,1,'2017-04-06 11:34:32','2017-04-06 11:34:32','Godfrey is a Medical Doctor and Public Health specialist by training currently working with METS as Program Officer-Ministry of Health Liaison. Before joining METS, he worked with Kibaale District Local Government as a medical doctor and assistant District Director of Health Services from 1998. For over 15 years Godfrey has worked with various organizations and agencies. His professional interest lies in the areas of public health systems strengthening and prevention with particular focus on in-service training and mentorship of health workers, policy development, health systems planning, monitoring and evaluation in the areas of HIV/AIDS, Communicable Diseases, Reproductive Health, Malaria and Child Health.\r\n\r\nHis other aptitude lies in applying multi-disciplinary epidemiological approaches, public health research design and, data analysis using Statistical Package for Social Scientists (SPSS) and Epidata. The pillars of his success have been his ability to communicate effectively, team work, flexibility towards different working conditions and ability to learn from past experiences. Godfrey holds a MBchB, MPH, and a Certificate in Orthopaedics and Trauma Surgery.','Dr. Godfrey Timbihurira