gaba','','','2017-07-10 15:52:29','2017-07-10 15:52:29','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=8760',0,'team-member','',0),(8761,2,'2017-04-07 09:56:45','2017-04-07 09:56:45','','Charity TN','','inherit','open','closed','','charity-tn','','','2017-04-07 09:56:45','2017-04-07 09:56:45','',8760,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Charity-TN.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8762,2,'2017-04-07 09:57:12','2017-04-07 09:57:12','','Charity Kyomugisha-Nuwagaba','','inherit','open','closed','','charity-kyomugisha-nuwagaba-2','','','2017-04-07 09:57:12','2017-04-07 09:57:12','',8760,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Charity-Kyomugisha-Nuwagaba.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8763,2,'2017-04-07 10:05:39','2017-04-07 10:05:39','','Charity TN','','inherit','open','closed','','charity-tn-2','','','2017-04-07 10:05:39','2017-04-07 10:05:39','',8760,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Charity-TN-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8764,2,'2017-04-07 10:23:28','2017-04-07 10:23:28','Stephen supports and coordinates the various software development activities including customizing national health information systems including DHIS2, OpenMRS; integrating fingerprinting technology for patient tracking, monitoring and referral across service sites; ensuring that electronic medical records systems and aggregate systems and patient’s tracker system are communicating by developing an interoperability framework for OpenMRS and DHIS2 in collaboration with the HIS Analysts; and ensuring that the different software developed conforms to the software development standards by conducting rigorous diagnosis, tests, code debugging, and documenting reference manuals.\r\n\r\nStephen is a Business and Technology Consultant who has worked with software development teams to deliver custom software for various clients. He has assisted customers identify user and business needs, defined technical specifications to meet those needs, evaluated vendor capability and supervised implementation of complex IT systems. Stephen has previously worked with Styx Technology Group, ThoughtWorks, Mercy Corps among many others.\r\n\r\nHe is passionate about growing the technology community in Uganda and on the Africa continent through “Coded in Africa, for Africans by Africans”. A personal goal in this journey is working towards having women as equal participants in the African technology revolution.\r\n\r\nStephen holds a Bachelor of Science in Civil Engineering\r\n\r\nWebsite: ssmusoke.com\r\n\r\nEmail: smusoke@musph.ac.ug','Stephen Musoke Senkomago','','publish','closed','closed','','stephen-musoke-senkomago','','','2017-07-11 15:15:49','2017-07-11 15:15:49','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=8764',0,'team-member','',0),(8765,2,'2017-04-07 10:21:57','2017-04-07 10:21:57','','Stephen M. Senkomago TN','','inherit','open','closed','','stephen-m-senkomago-tn','','','2017-04-07 10:21:57','2017-04-07 10:21:57','',8764,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Stephen-M.-Senkomago-TN.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8766,2,'2017-04-07 10:22:33','2017-04-07 10:22:33','','Stephen M. Senkomago','','inherit','open','closed','','stephen-m-senkomago','','','2017-04-07 10:22:33','2017-04-07 10:22:33','',8764,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Stephen-M.-Senkomago.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8767,2,'2017-04-07 10:33:58','2017-04-07 10:33:58','Email:mmurungi@musph.ac.ug','Dr. Miriam Murungi','','publish','closed','closed','','dr-miriam-murungi','','','2017-07-12 13:47:47','2017-07-12 13:47:47','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=8767',0,'team-member','',0),(8768,2,'2017-04-07 10:33:04','2017-04-07 10:33:04','','Dr. Miriam Murungi TN','','inherit','open','closed','','dr-miriam-murungi-tn','','','2017-04-07 10:33:04','2017-04-07 10:33:04','',8767,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Dr.-Miriam-Murungi-TN.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8769,2,'2017-04-07 10:33:43','2017-04-07 10:33:43','','Dr.-Miriam-Murungi','','inherit','open','closed','','dr-miriam-murungi-3','','','2017-04-07 10:33:43','2017-04-07 10:33:43','',8767,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Dr.-Miriam-Murungi.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8770,2,'2017-04-07 13:01:05','2017-04-07 13:01:05','Rose is a Monitoring and Evaluation (M&amp;E) specialist with over 10 years? experience. She has been involved in various undertakings in designing, coordinating, implementing and evaluating Public Health and other development programs. She is currently working as the Program Coordinator - District Led Programming (DLP) on the METS Program\r\n\r\nRose has provided technical support to various organizations and Districts to strengthen/establish M&amp;E systems through the development of costed M&amp;E plans that articulate the overall framework through which progress and performance of programs/projects is tracked.\r\n\r\nIn support of health systems strengthening, Rose has facilitated strategic planning workshops at National and District levels to guide the development of five year evidence based Strategic Plans for the HIV/AIDS program. She has also designed and conducted numerous evaluation studies aimed at informing the design of programs/projects as well as establishing progress and performance against set objectives.\r\n\r\nRose holds a Master of Arts degree in Demography and a Bachelors Degree in Social Sciences.','Rose Baryamutuma','','publish','closed','closed','','rose-baryamutuma','','','2017-07-11 15:09:43','2017-07-11 15:09:43','',0,'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=8770',0,'team-member','',0),(8771,2,'2017-04-07 13:00:03','2017-04-07 13:00:03','','Rose Baryamutuma TN','','inherit','open','closed','','rose-baryamutuma-tn','','','2017-04-07 13:00:03','2017-04-07 13:00:03','',8770,'http://mets.or.ug/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Rose-Baryamutuma-TN.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8772,2,'2017-04-07 13:00:37','2017-04-07 13:00:37'